data.description: The recreation space on the lower level has turned into a gathering area for your book club, your children and their friends, and even the dogs love to run around and play down there. The additional powder room is a great feature because you don't have to run up a level to use the bathroom. The main level also has a powder room off the dining area, which is on the front of the house. The dining table has turned into homework central afterschool, which is convenient because you can make dinner in the nearby gourmet kitchen and still be available for homework help. You can also keep an eye on the news from your big screen television in the family room on the other side of the kitchen. The open architecture of this floor makes your day-to-day life easier. At bedtime, on the upper level, you collect the dirty clothes and toss them in the washer located just down the hall. How convenient it is to have the laundry room so close by? Each of the two bedrooms at the front of the home have large closets and share a full bath off the hallway. Your primary suite is a dream come true with a large walk-in closet and an primary bath with double sinks and a separate commode area with a door. *Photos are of a similar home Some of the options featured in this home include: fourth level loft, gourmet kitchen, lower level powder room, oak stairs
